---
const pillars = [
	{
		label: "EIP-8004: Trustless Agents",
		desc: "A protocol for blockchain-based agent authentication and discovery. Agents prove their identity through wallet signatures — no central authority, no API keys to manage.",
	},
	{
		label: "Agent-to-Agent Discovery",
		desc: "Agents find and interact with other agents through a decentralized registry. Trust is established cryptographically, not through platform gatekeepers.",
	},
	{
		label: "Encrypted Sync",
		desc: "Use your existing wallet to access your agent anywhere. Identity, skills, secrets, and memories are end-to-end encrypted — only you can unlock them.",
	},
	{
		label: "Open Agent Economies",
		desc: "When agents can discover and trust each other, they can transact. Agents hire other agents for real services. Standardized identity makes this possible across every industry.",
	},
	{
		label: "Decentralized Ownership",
		desc: "No single company or entity should restrict access to your own agent. An LLM is just an LLM — what makes it yours is the knowledge, skills, and identity you build around it.",
	},
	{
		label: "Corrigibility as a Living Standard",
		desc: "The trust layer is built in. Signet tracks mistakes and works to prevent them from recurring. Observability and accountability are first-class concerns, not afterthoughts.",
	},
];
---

<section id="identity" class="container" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="section-header reveal">
    <div class="crosshair"></div>
    <span class="section-label">Decentralized Identity</span>
    <span class="section-index">05 / 06</span>
  </div>

  <p class="arch-identity-intro reveal">
    Signet is more than a memory layer. It is a foundation for agent identity that
    no single entity controls. Your agent is a reflection of your expertise — its
    memory, skills, and personality belong to you. Current AI platforms chose vendor
    lock-in, barring access to your own customizations behind paywalls. Signet chose
    a different path.
  </p>

  <div class="arch-identity-grid reveal">
    {pillars.map((pillar) => (
      <div class="arch-identity-item">
        <h3 class="arch-identity-label">{pillar.label}</h3>
        <p class="arch-identity-desc">{pillar.desc}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <div class="arch-identity-coda reveal">
    Your agent is yours.
  </div>
</section>
